      <hedline>
        <hl1>Watching the Paint Dry</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Nancy A Ranson letter says it would be great if the Web site that allows one to watch corn grow (June 22 article) also allows one to hear it grow</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In the summer of 1952, when my husband and I lived in Princeton, N.J., a friend told us that corn grows so fast you can hear it. So one night we all went out to a cornfield and lay down under the stars, listening to the ears of corn pop and crackle as they grew. We are delighted to read that there is a Web site for watching corn grow. We wonder whether it can be heard online.</p>
        <p>NANCY A. RANSOM  Nashville</p>
      </block>
